10409A(d)(1) of the Animal Health Protection Act to provide
$30,000,000 in mandatory funding for each of the fiscal years 2023
through 2025, from the Commodity Credit Corporation, to carry out
animal disease prevention and management. Of the $30,000,000
provided in funding, no less than $18,000,000 should be made
available for each fiscal year to carry out the National Animal Dis-
ease Preparedness and Response Program.
