Chairman Glenn ‘GT’ Thompson offered an opening statement as
did Ranking Member Craig. Without objection the Committee on
Agriculture Committee Print was placed before the Committee for
consideration and the first reading of the measure was waived.
Chairman Thompson informed members that pursuant to com-
mittee rule III(i)(2) and House Rule XI, Clause 2, the chair may
postpone further proceedings on the question of approving any
measure, matter, or adoption of an amendment on which a re-
