Meanwhile, after years of minimal growth, electricity demand in
the United States is projected to grow nationally at a significant
rate through the end of the decade.5 Over the past several decades,
the electric grid experienced modest demand for electric power,
averaging about 0.5 percent growth per year since 2015; however,
recent estimates show annual growth rate ranging between 3.7 per-
