Subtitle A—Energy, Providing for Reconciliation Pursuant to H.
Con. Res. 14
Subtitle A contains billions of dollars of cuts to Inflation Reduc-
tion Act programs designed to enhance American energy security
and reduce costs. It also contains overhauls to permitting policies
at the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) and Depart-
ment of Energy (DOE) and grants FERC brand-new powers to
grant crude oil, petroleum product, hydrogen, and carbon dioxide
pipeline developers eminent domain authority. It creates a de-risk-
