proceedings have already begun, the Doyle Memo instructed ICE
attorneys to seek to dismiss proceedings or ‘‘consider alternative
forms of prosecutorial discretion, including administrative closure,
stipulations to issues or relief, continuances, not pursuing an ap-
peal, joining motions to reopen, and stipulations in bond hear-
