In addition to the APA, another existing law governing—and de-
signed to constrain—agency action is the Congressional Review Act
(CRA) of 1996,294 which was part of then-Speaker Newt Gingrich’s
Contract With America legislative agenda.295 The CRA requires
agencies to submit rules to Congress and the U.S. Government Ac-
countability Office (GAO) before they can take effect, and it creates
